            <p>S. MORAIS&#44;<lb/>
                546 N. FIFTH STREET&#44;<lb/>
                PHILADELPHIA&#44; PA.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr William Pepper<lb/>
                Respected Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I fear that I have not expressed<lb/> myself clearly enough with regard to the position<lb/> of Isaac Husik.  <hi rend="underline">He is</hi> a student of<lb/> Hebrew literature&#44; under the auspices of the Jewish<lb/> Theological Seminary of New York&#44; in which he<lb/> is formally matriculated as a student.<lb/></p>
            <p>In my capacity of President of the Faculty and Director<lb/> of the Branch of the Jewish Theological association&#44; es&#45;<lb/>&#45;tablished in Philadelphia&#44; I have undertaken to instruct<lb/> him and another lad&#44; who is also enrolled as a pupil.<lb/>  Both will graduate from the Jewish Theological Seminary<lb/> of New York&#44; when their knowledge and their respective<lb/> age will warrant it.<lb/>
                With a deep sense of gratitude for your kindness&#44; I beg<lb/> to return the order for a gratuity&#44; and venture to trouble<lb/> you again with an application for a free scholarship.<lb/>  Without pledging my word for it&#44; I may say that assistance<lb/> to the scholarship fund at the hands of my coreligionists&#44; <del>in the</del><lb/> <del>near future</del>&#59; will possibly come in the near future Yours truly<lb/> S Morais<lb/></p>
            </body>
